<collectingRegion id="AE158DE9FFACFFF2F8A2AD2C832FFDB8" box="[727,842,578,604]" country="Brazil" name="Sao Paulo" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">São Paulo</collectingRegion>
include Santos and Guarujá (
<bibRefCitation id="08403EFAFFACFFF2FEE8AD2C8093FD64" author="Severino-Rodrigues, E. &amp; Hebling, N. J. &amp; Graca-Lopes, R." pageId="24" pageNumber="25" pagination="171 - 182" refId="ref78241" refString="Severino-Rodrigues, E., Hebling, N. J. &amp; Graca-Lopes, R. (2007) Biodiversidade no produto da pesca de arrasto-de-fundo dirigida ao lagostim, Metanephrops rubellus (Moreira, 1903), desembarcado no litoral do estado de Sao Paulo, Brasil. Boletim do Instituto de Pesca, 33 (2), 171 - 182." type="journal article" year="2007">
Severino-Rodrigues 
<emphasis id="5EA59F19FFACFFF2FFFDAD2D80D1FD64" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">et al.</emphasis>
2007
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="08403EFAFFACFFF2FB77AD0881B4FD64" author="Duarte, L. F. A. &amp; Severino-Rodrigues, E. &amp; Gasalla, M. A." box="[258,465,614,640]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" pagination="141 - 151" refId="ref61295" refString="Duarte, L. F. A., Severino-Rodrigues, E. &amp; Gasalla, M. A. (2010) Slipper lobster (Crustacea, Decapoda, Scyllaridae) fisheries off the southeastern coast of Brazil: I. Exploitation patterns between 23 ° 00 ' and 29 ° 65 ' S. Fisheries Research, 102, 141 - 151. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. fishres. 2009.11.004" type="journal article" year="2010">
Duarte 
<emphasis id="5EA59F19FFACFFF2FB20AD0981E8FD64" box="[341,397,614,640]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">et al.</emphasis>
2010
</bibRefCitation>
). In 
<collectingCountry id="14C6039BFFACFFF2F874AD08822DFD64" box="[513,584,614,640]" name="Brazil" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, there is no established fishery for any of the 
<taxonomicName id="ABD13888FFACFFF2FE33AD08855EFD64" authority="Gill, 1898" authorityName="Gill" authorityYear="1898" box="[1094,1339,614,640]" class="Malacostraca" family="Scyllaridae" genus="Scyllarides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5EA59F19FFACFFF2FE33AD0884A7FD64" box="[1094,1218,614,640]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Scyllarides</emphasis>
Gill, 1898
</taxonomicName>
Western Central Atlantic species, which are fished locally or caught incidentally as bycatch during spiny lobster fisheries and may be sold in local markets (
<bibRefCitation id="08403EFAFFACFFF2F856ADC0829FFD2C" author="Duarte, L. F. A. &amp; Severino-Rodrigues, E. &amp; Gasalla, M. A." box="[547,762,686,712]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" pagination="141 - 151" refId="ref61295" refString="Duarte, L. F. A., Severino-Rodrigues, E. &amp; Gasalla, M. A. (2010) Slipper lobster (Crustacea, Decapoda, Scyllaridae) fisheries off the southeastern coast of Brazil: I. Exploitation patterns between 23 ° 00 ' and 29 ° 65 ' S. Fisheries Research, 102, 141 - 151. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. fishres. 2009.11.004" type="journal article" year="2010">
Duarte 
<emphasis id="5EA59F19FFACFFF2F80FADC182D1FD2C" box="[634,692,686,712]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">et al.</emphasis>
2010
</bibRefCitation>
). Nevertheless, 
<taxonomicName id="ABD13888FFACFFF2F9DAADC08428FD2C" authorityName="Rathbun" authorityYear="1906" box="[943,1101,686,712]" class="Malacostraca" family="Scyllaridae" genus="Scyllarides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brasiliensis">
<emphasis id="5EA59F19FFACFFF2F9DAADC08428FD2C" box="[943,1101,686,712]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">S. brasiliensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is becoming one of the most commercially important species in South America, especially in the north-east region (
<bibRefCitation id="08403EFAFFACFFF2FEF8ADBC85FDFD08" author="Santos, M. C. F. &amp; Freitas, A. E. T. S." box="[1165,1432,722,748]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" pagination="123 - 143" refId="ref77210" refString="Santos, M. C. F. &amp; Freitas, A. E. T. S. (2002) Estudo sobre a lagosta sapata Scyllarides brasiliensis Rathbun, 1906 (Crustacea: Decapoda: Scyllaridae) no litoral dos estados de Pernambuco e Alagoas, Brasil. Boletim Tecnico Cientifico do CEPENE, 10 (1), 123 - 143." type="journal article" year="2002">Santos &amp; Freitas 2002</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="08403EFAFFACFFF2FAE2AD9881A2FCF4" author="Rodriguez-Rey, G. T. &amp; Sole-Cava, A. M. &amp; Lazoski, C." box="[151,455,758,784]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" pagination="59 - 69" refId="ref76221" refString="Rodriguez-Rey, G. T., Sole-Cava, A. M. &amp; Lazoski, C. (2014) Genetic homogeneity and historical expansions of the slipper lobster, Scyllarides brasiliensis, in the south-west Atlantic. Marine and Freshwater Research, 65, 59 - 69. https: // doi. org / 10.1071 / MF 12359" type="journal article" year="2014">
Rodríguez-Rey 
<emphasis id="5EA59F19FFACFFF2FB3FAD9981E6FCF4" box="[330,387,758,784]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">et al.</emphasis>
2014
</bibRefCitation>
). The genetic homogeneity among the populations of 
<taxonomicName id="ABD13888FFACFFF2FE51AD9884A7FCF4" authorityName="Rathbun" authorityYear="1906" box="[1060,1218,758,784]" class="Malacostraca" family="Scyllaridae" genus="Scyllarides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brasiliensis">
<emphasis id="5EA59F19FFACFFF2FE51AD9884A7FCF4" box="[1060,1218,758,784]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">S. brasiliensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
along the 
<quantity id="AB29EEEEFFACFFF2FF4CAD9885F9FCF4" box="[1337,1436,758,784]" metricMagnitude="6" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.7" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" unit="km" value="2700.0">2700 km</quantity>
from 
<collectingRegion id="AE158DE9FFACFFF2FAA0AC748173FCD0" box="[213,278,794,820]" country="Brazil" name="Ceara" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Ceará</collectingRegion>
to 
<collectingRegion id="AE158DE9FFACFFF2FB4CAC7481BCFCD0" box="[313,473,794,820]" country="Brazil" name="Espirito Santo" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Espírito Santo</collectingRegion>
coasts could be explained based on traits that favor dispersion, such as high fecundity and long planktonic phases associated with ocean currents (
<bibRefCitation id="08403EFAFFACFFF2F947AC50843AFCBC" author="Rodriguez-Rey, G. T. &amp; Sole-Cava, A. M. &amp; Lazoski, C." box="[818,1119,830,856]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" pagination="59 - 69" refId="ref76221" refString="Rodriguez-Rey, G. T., Sole-Cava, A. M. &amp; Lazoski, C. (2014) Genetic homogeneity and historical expansions of the slipper lobster, Scyllarides brasiliensis, in the south-west Atlantic. Marine and Freshwater Research, 65, 59 - 69. https: // doi. org / 10.1071 / MF 12359" type="journal article" year="2014">
Rodríguez-Rey 
<emphasis id="5EA59F19FFACFFF2F991AC518479FCBC" box="[996,1052,830,856]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">et al.</emphasis>
2014
</bibRefCitation>
). Knowledge about this species is scarce, information about its biology and fishery is still lacking. Furthermore, this species has no economic importance despite being caught in association with other lobsters (
<bibRefCitation id="08403EFAFFACFFF2F9E4ACE884C1FC44" author="Fausto Filho, J. &amp; Matthews, H. R. &amp; Lima, H. H." box="[913,1188,902,928]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" pagination="127 - 130" refId="ref62099" refString="Fausto Filho, J., Matthews, H. R. &amp; Lima, H. H. (1966) Nota preliminar sobre a fauna dos bancos de lagostas no Ceara. Arquivos da Estacao de Biologia Marinha da Universidade Federal Ceara, 6 (2), 127 - 130. https: // doi. org / 10.32360 / acmar. v 6 i 2.329" type="journal article" year="1966">
Fausto Filho 
<emphasis id="5EA59F19FFACFFF2FE5DACE9843EFC44" box="[1064,1115,902,928]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">et al</emphasis>
. 1966
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="08403EFAFFACFFF2FEC4ACE88531FC44" author="Holthuis, L. B." box="[1201,1364,902,928]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" pagination="1 - 292" refId="ref64998" refString="Holthuis, L. B. (1991) Marine lobsters of the world. An annotated and illustrated catalogue of species of interest to fisheries known to date. FAO Fisheries Synopsis, 125 (13), 1 - 292." type="journal article" year="1991">Holthuis 1991</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="08403EFAFFACFFF2FF14ACE880B7FC20" author="Melo, G. A. S." pageId="24" pageNumber="25" refId="ref69664" refString="Melo, G. A. S. (1999) Manual de identificacao dos Crustacea Decapoda do litoral brasileiro: Anomura, Thalassinidea, Palinuridea, Astacidea. Ed. Pleidae, Sao Paulo, 551 pp." type="book" year="1999">Melo 1999</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="08403EFAFFACFFF2FAABACC481BEFC20" author="Santos, M. C. F. &amp; Freitas, A. E. T. S." box="[222,475,938,964]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" pagination="123 - 143" refId="ref77210" refString="Santos, M. C. F. &amp; Freitas, A. E. T. S. (2002) Estudo sobre a lagosta sapata Scyllarides brasiliensis Rathbun, 1906 (Crustacea: Decapoda: Scyllaridae) no litoral dos estados de Pernambuco e Alagoas, Brasil. Boletim Tecnico Cientifico do CEPENE, 10 (1), 123 - 143." type="journal article" year="2002">Santos &amp; Freitas 2002</bibRefCitation>
). The occurrence of 
<taxonomicName id="ABD13888FFACFFF2F8CBACC4833EFC20" authorityName="Rathbun" authorityYear="1906" box="[702,859,938,964]" class="Malacostraca" family="Scyllaridae" genus="Scyllarides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brasiliensis">
<emphasis id="5EA59F19FFACFFF2F8CBACC4833EFC20" box="[702,859,938,964]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">S. brasiliensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the distribution limits along the Brazilian coast proposed by 
<bibRefCitation id="08403EFAFFACFFF2FB5CACA081D5FC0C" author="Melo, G. A. S." box="[297,432,974,1000]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" refId="ref69664" refString="Melo, G. A. S. (1999) Manual de identificacao dos Crustacea Decapoda do litoral brasileiro: Anomura, Thalassinidea, Palinuridea, Astacidea. Ed. Pleidae, Sao Paulo, 551 pp." type="book" year="1999">Melo (1999</bibRefCitation>
, Fig. 301, p. 448) suggest that this species is more prevalent to the north of 
<collectingRegion id="AE158DE9FFACFFF2FF72ACA0851EFC0C" box="[1287,1403,974,1000]" country="Brazil" name="Sao Paulo" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">São Paulo</collectingRegion>
, in the 
<geoCoordinate id="09E525CCFFACFFF2FAB4AC9D817CFBEA" box="[193,281,1011,1038]" degrees="23" direction="south" minutes="30" orientation="latitude" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" precision="925" value="-23.5">23°30′S</geoCoordinate>
<geoCoordinate id="09E525CCFFACFFF2FB54AC9D81E1FBEA" box="[289,388,1011,1038]" degrees="43" direction="west" minutes="00" orientation="longitude" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" precision="925" value="-43.0">43°00′W</geoCoordinate>
to 
<geoCoordinate id="09E525CCFFACFFF2FBDDAC9D8264FBEA" box="[424,513,1011,1038]" degrees="24" direction="south" minutes="19" orientation="latitude" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" precision="925" value="-24.316668">24°19′S</geoCoordinate>
<geoCoordinate id="09E525CCFFACFFF2F87DAC9D820EFBEA" box="[520,619,1011,1038]" degrees="45" direction="west" minutes="09" orientation="longitude" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" precision="925" value="-45.15">45°09′W</geoCoordinate>
, and in 
<quantity id="AB29EEEEFFACFFF2F8B1AC9C8350FBE8" box="[708,821,1010,1037]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.75" metricValueMax="13.0" metricValueMin="4.5" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" unit="m" value="87.5" valueMax="130.0" valueMin="45.0">45–130 m</quantity>
depths (
<bibRefCitation id="08403EFAFFACFFF2F9E6AC9C8401FBE8" author="Duarte, L. F. A. &amp; Severino-Rodrigues, E. &amp; Gasalla, M. A." box="[915,1124,1010,1036]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" pagination="141 - 151" refId="ref61295" refString="Duarte, L. F. A., Severino-Rodrigues, E. &amp; Gasalla, M. A. (2010) Slipper lobster (Crustacea, Decapoda, Scyllaridae) fisheries off the southeastern coast of Brazil: I. Exploitation patterns between 23 ° 00 ' and 29 ° 65 ' S. Fisheries Research, 102, 141 - 151. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. fishres. 2009.11.004" type="journal article" year="2010">
Duarte 
<emphasis id="5EA59F19FFACFFF2F99DAC9D8444FBE8" box="[1000,1057,1010,1036]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">et al.</emphasis>
2010
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="08403EFAFFACFFF2FE1AAC9C8551FBE8" author="Cintra, I. H. A. &amp; de Araujo Silva, K. C. &amp; Martins, D. E. G. &amp; Santos, W. C. R. &amp; Klautau, A. G. C. M. &amp; Alves-Junior, F. A." box="[1135,1332,1010,1036]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" pagination="71 - 72" refId="ref57990" refString="Cintra, I. H. A., de Araujo Silva, K. C., Martins, D. E. G., Santos, W. C. R., Klautau, A. G. C. M. &amp; Alves-Junior, F. A. (2021) Report of slipper lobster Scyllarides brasiliensis Rathbun, 1906 (Decapoda: Scyllaridae) in the Great Amazon Reef System, Para, Brazil. Biota Amazonia, 11 (2), 71 - 72. https: // doi. org / 10.18561 / 2179 - 5746 / biotaamazonia. v 11 n 2 p 71 - 72" type="journal article" year="2021">
Cintra 
<emphasis id="5EA59F19FFACFFF2FEC9AC9D8491FBE8" box="[1212,1268,1010,1036]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">et al.</emphasis>
2021
</bibRefCitation>
) and it is more frequent and abundant in the northeast region (
<bibRefCitation id="08403EFAFFACFFF2F896AB788386FBD4" author="Santos, M. C. F. &amp; Freitas, A. E. T. S." box="[739,995,1046,1072]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" pagination="123 - 143" refId="ref77210" refString="Santos, M. C. F. &amp; Freitas, A. E. T. S. (2002) Estudo sobre a lagosta sapata Scyllarides brasiliensis Rathbun, 1906 (Crustacea: Decapoda: Scyllaridae) no litoral dos estados de Pernambuco e Alagoas, Brasil. Boletim Tecnico Cientifico do CEPENE, 10 (1), 123 - 143." type="journal article" year="2002">Santos &amp; Freitas 2002</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
